---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';

const title = 'Terms of use';
const description =
  'Terms governing your use of the aprioristudio.com website. Plain English summary of what you can and cannot do here.';
const updated = '2026-05-04';
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5 py-10 md:py-14">
    <Breadcrumbs items={[
      { href: '/', label: 'Home' },
      { href: '/terms', label: 'Terms of use' },
    ]} />

    <header class="mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Terms of use</h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[var(--color-ink-soft)]">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose-body">
      <p>
        These terms govern your use of aprioristudio.com, the website operated by Apriori Ltd, a
        private limited company registered in England and Wales. By using the site, you agree
        to these terms. If you don't agree, please don't use the site.
      </p>
      <p>
        These terms cover the website only. They are not the contract under which we deliver
        client work — that's a separate written agreement signed before any project begins.
      </p>

      <h2>What this site is</h2>
      <p>
        aprioristudio.com is a marketing website describing the services we offer (web and
        mobile app development) and a way to get in touch with us. The information here is for
        general informational purposes. It's not a contract, an offer, or professional advice.
        We update content from time to time without notice.
      </p>

      <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>
        You may view the site, follow links, and submit the contact form for legitimate
        enquiries. You may not:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use the contact form to send spam, marketing, or automated submissions</li>
        <li>Attempt to probe, scan, or test the security of the site or attempt to breach security or authentication measures</li>
        <li>Try to overload the site (denial-of-service attacks, mass scraping, etc.)</li>
        <li>Use the site or its contents in any way that breaks UK law</li>
        <li>Reverse-engineer, decompile, or copy any part of the site for commercial purposes without written permission</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>
        All content on this website — text, images, logos, code, design — is owned by Apriori
        Ltd or used under licence, and is protected by UK and international copyright law. You
        may quote short excerpts for non-commercial purposes (a review, a citation, a social
        media post linking back to us) provided you credit the source. Republishing whole pages,
        copying our logo, or imitating our design for commercial purposes requires written
        permission.
      </p>

      <h2>Links to other websites</h2>
      <p>
        The site may contain links to third-party websites for reference. We don't control
        those sites, we don't endorse their content, and we're not responsible for them. If you
        follow an external link, you do so at your own risk and are subject to their terms and
        privacy policies, not ours.
      </p>

      <h2>Disclaimers and limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        We try to keep the site accurate and up to date but make no warranties that all content
        is current, complete, or error-free. The site is provided "as is." We don't accept
        liability for any loss or damage arising from your use of (or inability to use) this
        website, except where such liability cannot be excluded under UK law (for example,
        liability for death or personal injury caused by negligence).
      </p>

      <h2>Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Use of the site is also governed by our <a href="/privacy">privacy policy</a>, which
        explains what personal information we collect and how we use it.
      </p>

      <h2>Governing law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are governed by the laws of England and Wales. Any dispute arising in
        connection with these terms is subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of
        England and Wales.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to these terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these terms from time to time. The "last updated" date at the top of this
        page reflects the most recent change. By continuing to use the site after an update,
        you accept the revised terms.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these terms can be sent to
        <a href="mailto:mp@aprioristudio.com">mp@aprioristudio.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
